cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use these transcription-factor couplings or the cell-cycle rate multiplier, please cite this work and the source data (Teufel et al. 2019)."
title: "tf-coupling-fit: transcription-factor coupling strengths and a mean-preserving cell-cycle rate multiplier for Saccharomyces cerevisiae"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Segal
    given-names: Daniel J.
url: "https://github.com/djsegal/tf-coupling-fit"
repository-code: "https://github.com/djsegal/tf-coupling-fit"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - transcription factor
  - gene regulatory network
  - cell cycle
  - Saccharomyces cerevisiae
  - whole-cell model
abstract: >-
  Per-edge transcription-factor coupling strengths for budding yeast, fit by an
  L1-regularized linear program, together with a mean-preserving multiplier that
  turns the couplings into a cell-cycle-dependent transcription rate without
  changing each gene's average rate. The couplings are derived from the RNA-seq
  time course and regulatory network of Teufel et al. 2019.
references:
  - type: article
    title: "A transcriptome-wide analysis deciphers distinct roles of G1 cyclins in temporal organization of the yeast cell cycle"
    authors:
      - family-names: Teufel
        given-names: Lotte
      - family-names: Tummler
        given-names: Katja
      - family-names: Flöttmann
        given-names: Max
      - family-names: Herrmann
        given-names: Andreas
      - family-names: Barkai
        given-names: Naama
      - family-names: Klipp
        given-names: Edda
    journal: "Scientific Reports"
    year: 2019
    volume: 9
    start: 3343
    doi: "10.1038/s41598-019-39850-7"
